  <a href="#1" id="1">
   MONUMENTS AND SQUARES
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   Dawn broke on May 27, 1989 over a battle-scarred Tiananmen Square with tanks and rifle-toting troops ruling the vast expanse occupied the day before by students seeking a freer society from their communist rulers.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   Gunfire could be heard from several sides, and tracers zipped through the sky above Mao Tse-tung's mausoleum, one of the main monuments to Chinese communism in the square.
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   Hundreds of helmeted troops were deployed on the monument to revolutionary heroes in the square's center and thousands more at important intersections nearby.
  </a>
